 and running again ewan seeks help from laura the former owners daughter and he quickly feels a connection with her but shes being courted by another mana lawyer with far more social clout and money than ewan resolving that hell make the brickworks enough of a success that he can become a partner in the business and be able to afford to bring his sisters over from ireland ewan pours all his energy into the new job but when hugh signs a bad business deal all ewans hard work is put in jeopardy as his hopes for the future crumble laura reveals something surprising can she help him save the brickworks and will ewan finally get a shot at winning her heart author bio▼▲ judith miller is an awardwinning writer whose avid research and love for history are reflected in her bestselling novels she is the author of the popular daughters of amana and home to amana series which explore the closed communities of iowas amana colonies judy makes her home in topekakansas learn more at wwwjudithmccoymillercom product reviews▼▲  stars out of   out of   stars   stars   stars   stars   star  quality  out of   out of  value  out of   out of  meets expectations  out of   out of   of customers would recommend this product to a friend write review sort by most recent overall rating helpfulness see    displaying items  of  page  of   next last debbie from christfocus harrison ar age  gender female  stars out of  nice brickmaking details but the writing had some problems february   debbie from christfocus harrison ar age  gender female quality  value  meets expectations  this review was written for the brickmakers bride refined by love series  the brickmakers bride is a historical novel set in  the author described many details about how bricks were made and she worked in historical details like how the recent civil war affected the number of skilled laborers that were available for ewan to hire i found the main characters interesting but i felt like the story started in one direction and then headed in another it seemed like a story about ewan not having the highclass social skills need to get contracts for the brickyard and feeling not worthy of the laura meanwhile laura thinks he wont want to marry her if he knew her secret ewans situation didnt really change but the storys focus changed to the troubles that ewan has at the brickyard i was exasperated that ewan was so selfrighteous about his not pursuing laura while someone else was courting her and then hes suddenly kissing her in the open at a work site and then kisses her again before they start courting and again before she agrees to marry him but hes not very understanding toward a relative who is tempted by a handsome man ewan also started out with a strong faith in god yet he ended up more anxious about things than his unbelieving uncle finally i was disappointed that the author often skipped scenes that shed built up to for example ewan is worried how his uncle will take some news and laura promises to support him during the confrontation andwe skip that whole confrontation there was no sex or bad language overall id recommend this book to fans of historical novels was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate wfnren st cloud fl age  gender female  stars out of  another great book by judith january   wfnren st cloud fl age  gender female quality  value  meets expectations  a great story that shows how faith can get you through anything i have enjoyed judiths books in the past and this can be added to my list of books that i really liked judith does a wonderful job of pulling you into the story maybe wanting to slap someone really hard many times even oh yes you have to read to see how cruel one person can be was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate caroljo farmington mo age over  gender female  stars out of  god gives us the desires of our heart april   caroljo farmington mo age over  gender female quality  value  meets expectations  this review was written for the brickmakers bride refined by love series  the brickmakers bride by judith miller is an excellent story of post civil war days in west virginia judith miller shares how difficult it was to run a brickmaking operation when most of the men had been killed in the war or no longer able to do manual labor you will feel ewan mckays desperation to make the operation a success and to bring his younger sisters from ireland judith miller has done an great job of making you feel the frustrations and pain as well as love and joy felt by the characters in this book the story was easy to follow i was given this book by bethany house and thoroughly enjoyed it was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate lucy wv age  gender female  stars out of  judith miller at her best march   lucy wv age  gender female this review was written for the brickmakers bride refined by love series  whats not to lovehistory my state wv a little romancejudith miller doesnt fail to impress me with her masterful way of telling a story and teaching our history at the same time i throughly enjoyed this book and the characters i recommend this to anyone who loves historical fiction was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate nica age  gender female  stars out of  not what i was hoping for march   nica age  gender female this review was written for the brickmakers bride refined by love series  i really wanted to like this book but sadly it was not my favorite however the historical content was interesting as was learning about the brickmaking business the main character laura and her mother sell their brickmaking business to ewan and his uncle who have a tenuous relationship they dont agree on how to run the business which creates conflict ewan wants to run the company in the best and wisest way possible so laura agrees to help as she grew up in the business and is very knowledgeable there are other characters in the book but they cause a lot of conflict and drama i found that annoyed me which is one of the reasons i did not like this book i give this book  out of  stars as it was well written but not an enjoyable read as i would have liked i received a free copy of this book from bethany house in exchange for an honest review was this review helpful helpful votes yes   no  flag as inappropriate displaying items  of  page  of   next last ask a question▼▲ have a question about this product ask us here find related products▼▲ books ebooks  audio  fiction  historical books ebooks  audio  fiction  romance  historical romance books ebooks  audio  ebooks  fiction  historical books ebooks  audio  ebooks  fiction  romance  historical romance download  ebooks  fiction authorartist review▼▲ im the authorartist and i want to review the brickmakers bride refined by love series   ebook backtimes backtimes ask a question what would you like to know about this product please enter your name your email and your question regarding the product in the fields below and well answer you in the next  hours if you need immediate assistance regarding this product or any other please call christian to speak directly with a customer service representative name email question submit edit confirm sign up to receiveexclusive email offersyou can unsubscribe at any time sign up to receive exclusive email offersyou can unsubscribe at any time sign up connect with us account checkout account order history wishlist cart subscribe email unsubscribe email shipping  returns shipping  handling rates easy returns services affiliate program gift cards membership selfpublishing catalog catalog quick shop online catalogs request our catalogs community social media prayer wall author profiles about us company info job opportunities help customer service faq shops bibles homeschool bargains vbs christian living toys gifts kids dvds fiction music academics desktop site  christianoutside the united statesand canada call   email us  summit st pe